               <p style="color:rgb(253, 55, 154);font-size:18px;">
                The Pug is a small dog breed and reaches a height of around 26 to 34cm and an ideal weight of approx. 6.3 to 8.1 kg. Since the Pug is a so-called “brachycephalic” breed and struggles with respiratory problems due to its round-shaped head and short nose, excess weight should be avoided.
                You should make sure its food has an adapted amount of calories, since if not, the Pug can reach a higher weight than foreseen and develop an unstable bone structure.

                By nature, the Pug has a compact physique with good, strong muscles. Hence, it needs sufficient exercise and a balanced needs-based diet.
                In addition, you should keep an eye on the quantity of food, since a Pug won't stop eating of its own accord if there is still food in its bowl.
